    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Fiberboard that is typically made of wood dust or fibers, or other cellulose left over from the processing of other products; distinguished from medium-density fiberboard and high-density fiberboard by density of fiber and strength.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000000/VP</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000047822/MFA Conservation and Art Material Encyclopedia Online: CAMEO (2005-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Vezelplaat gemaakt van houtdeeltjes of -vezels, of van andere cellulose die overblijft als restmateriaal bij andere producten; heeft een lagere vezeldichtheid en sterkte dan mdf en hdf.
</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Dutch</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000205/AAT-Ned</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000113770/AAT-Ned (1994-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Placa de fibra  que é normalmente feita de pó de madeira ou fibras, ou outra celulose que sobrou do processamento de outros produtos; Distingue-se do painel de fibra de média densidade e do painel de fibra de alta densidade pela densidade da fibra e resistência.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Portuguese</Note_Language>
